There is a noticeable trend toward vegetarian diets and no fish consumption due to concerns about animal welfare, environmental sustainability, and personal health benefits associated with plant-based diets.

Cars are often used more for short journeys because they provide convenience, comfort, and flexibility in terms of route choice and timing.

Many people use a car every day to travel long distances to work because it is often more convenient, flexible, and time-efficient compared to other modes of transportation like public transit or biking.

The ability to capture video is a new phenomenon because advancements in technology have made it more accessible and affordable for the average person to record videos using smartphones, digital cameras, and other devices. Additionally, the rise of social media and video-sharing platforms has created a demand for easy-to-use video recording tools.

The creation and sharing of video content is an integral part of the modern lifestyle because it allows people to easily communicate, express themselves, entertain others, and consume information in a visually engaging and convenient format.
Men were historically smaller due to a combination of factors such as limited access to food, poor living conditions, and higher rates of disease and malnutrition.

Men are often taller than women due to genetic and hormonal differences, as well as evolutionary factors. Generally, men have higher levels of testosterone, which can contribute to increased muscle mass and bone density, leading to greater height. Additionally, taller men may have been more successful in attracting a mate and passing on their genes throughout human history, leading to the prevalence of height in men.
People are less physically active today due to various factors, including sedentary jobs, increased screen time, lack of access to safe outdoor spaces, and reliance on cars for transportation.

Exercise increases the blood pump because it causes the heart to beat faster and more forcefully, which in turn increases the flow of blood throughout the body to deliver oxygen and nutrients to tissues and remove waste products.

The proportion of motorways is high on European roads because they are designed to efficiently handle high volumes of traffic, improve safety, and facilitate long-distance travel across countries and regions. Additionally, motorways are an essential component of the European transportation network, connecting major cities and economic centers.
The speed limit on most European roads is low to prioritize safety and reduce accidents, especially in densely populated areas with narrow streets and heavy traffic.

Telecommunication technology is becoming more efficient due to advancements in hardware and software, increased network capacity, improved signal processing techniques, and the development of new communication protocols. These factors have contributed to faster data transmission speeds, higher quality audio and video calls, and more reliable connections.

The use of the Internet has increased dramatically in the recent past due to the growing popularity of online activities such as streaming videos, online shopping, social media, and remote work and learning. This increased demand has necessitated the expansion and improvement of technical infrastructure to support higher bandwidth and faster speeds to accommodate the growing number of users and data traffic.
Wireless data transfer allows for greater convenience, mobility, and flexibility in using devices and accessing information without the restrictions of cords or cables.
The production of electronic devices is at an all-time high due to increasing demand for technology, advancements in manufacturing processes, and the constant release of new and innovative products.

Humans are able to coordinate large tasks effectively due to their advanced cognitive abilities, such as communication, problem-solving skills, and ability to plan and organize complex activities. Additionally, humans have the capacity for empathy and cooperation, allowing them to work together towards a common goal.

The decline in mental arithmetic skills in the population may be attributed to the increased reliance on technology, such as calculators and smartphones, to perform mathematical calculations. This has resulted in decreased practice and proficiency in mental arithmetic. Additionally, changes in educational curricula and teaching methods may also play a role in the decline of mental arithmetic skills.

The ball travels a substantially smaller distance than a player runs in a game of soccer because the player is constantly changing direction, dribbling, passing, and making quick movements on the field, while the ball typically only moves when kicked or passed by a player.

Soccer has become faster and more dynamic in recent years due to advancements in sports science, technology, and tactics. Players are now faster, stronger, and more agile, allowing for quicker passing, movement, and decision-making on the field. Additionally, coaches have developed more sophisticated strategies and formations to exploit space and create scoring opportunities, leading to a more fast-paced and exciting style of play.

The human body has evolved to use air more efficiently in order to maximize the amount of oxygen that can be absorbed by the lungs and transported to the cells, where it is needed for energy production. This increased efficiency allows for better overall functioning of the body and improved physical performance.
The human body has evolved to require more air due to the increased metabolic demands of a larger brain and higher levels of physical activity.

Modern cities emphasize efficient use of water to ensure sustainable management of water resources, reduce strain on infrastructure, protect the environment, and mitigate the impacts of drought and water scarcity.

Modern lifestyles require very large amounts of water for various daily activities such as drinking, cooking, cleaning, irrigation, industry, and sanitation. Additionally, the use of water-intensive technologies and products, as well as the increasing population density in urban areas, contribute to the high demand for water in modern societies.

Disney makes shorter movies because they are typically targeted towards a younger audience with shorter attention spans. Additionally, shorter movies allow for more frequent screenings in theaters and can be more easily consumed by viewers at home.

Disney has historically had a large movie output due to its successful and diverse portfolio of intellectual properties, which includes iconic characters, franchises, and stories that appeal to a wide audience. Additionally, the company has a strong history of producing high-quality and innovative content, as well as a well-established distribution network that allows for extensive theatrical releases and international reach.

Grave goods have become unpopular in modern times due to changing beliefs and traditions surrounding death and burial practices, as well as increasing concerns about cultural appropriation and respecting the wishes of the deceased and their families.

Grave goods often have high monetary value because they are rare and historically significant artifacts that are typically associated with wealthy or high-status individuals. Additionally, the demand for such items among collectors and museums can drive up their value even further.

The world's entire ecosystem depends on a constant replenishment of oxygen because oxygen is essential for the process of respiration, which allows organisms to convert nutrients into energy. This process is necessary for the survival of all living organisms.

Humans can survive for longer periods at lower levels of oxygen because our bodies have the ability to adapt to lower oxygen levels through a process called acclimatization. This includes increasing red blood cell production, improving oxygen utilization in tissues, and adjusting breathing patterns to compensate for the lower oxygen levels.

The vast amount of human knowledge is dispersed because people have different experiences, backgrounds, and access to information sources, leading to diverse perspectives and areas of expertise. Additionally, knowledge is constantly evolving and being generated, further contributing to its dispersion.

Only a few species of spiders make webs because web-making is a specialized behavior that requires specific adaptations and skills. Spiders that do make webs have evolved to have specialized silk-producing organs and spinning techniques that allow them to create intricate and effective webs for catching prey. Other species of spiders have different hunting strategies and do not rely on webs to capture food.

Large spider webs are often found in homes because spiders are attracted to warm, dark, and secluded areas where they can catch prey easily. Homes provide an ideal environment for spiders to thrive and build their webs to catch insects for food.

The growth rate of trees is greater than one would expect due to a combination of factors such as favorable environmental conditions, genetic traits, and the ability of trees to efficiently convert sunlight, water, and nutrients into biomass through photosynthesis. New York has many open and green spaces due to city planning efforts to prioritize urban greenery, public parks, and recreational areas for residents and visitors to enjoy.

New York is mostly concrete with lots of skyscrapers due to its high population density, limited space for horizontal expansion, and the need to accommodate a large number of people and businesses in a small area.
